On October 25, 2007, the following article appeared in the New England Journal of Medicine: "Furlong's paper is the first study to show that mood-related changes in mood and behaviour occur only in mammals."  Furlong and co-authors published a new review and summary of the new research, published in the Journal of Neurobiology of Mood and Behaviour.  They found that "the brain's reward circuits respond to changes in the human mood state, including changes in anxiety arousal or anxiety-like symptoms, as well as changes in depression, anxiety disorder, and mood.
